import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='pct', by='region', grid=False)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Pct')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'pct' across different 'region'?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    groups = data['group'].unique()
    for group in groups:
        group_data = data[data['group'] == group]['pct']
        plt.hist(group_data, alpha=0.5, label=group)
    
    plt.xlabel('pct')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Group')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'pct' across different 'group'?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    name_count_by_region = data.groupby('region')['name'].count()
    name_count_by_region.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the count of 'name' in each 'region'?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
